<td valign="top" width="65%">
<p class="bodytxt" style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;">Did you love the time you spent at Ricks College and/or BYU&ndash;Idaho? Do you often find yourself reflecting back on your days in Rexburg? Have you ever encouraged a student to attend BYU&ndash;Idaho? Are you convinced the school is heading in the right direction? &nbsp;</span></span></p>
<p class="bodytxt" style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;">If so, you share many of the insights and feelings of over 200 BYU&ndash;Idaho Alumni Ambassadors currently serving throughout the United States and Canada. Our Ambassadors are alumni who feel passionately about the legacy of Ricks College and the future of BYU&ndash;Idaho. They encourage alumni, parents, friends, and students to discover or rekindle the &ldquo;Spirit of Ricks.&rdquo; Ambassadors are literally our eyes and ears as they:</span></span></p>
<ol>
<li>
<p class="bodytxt" style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;"> &nbsp;Represent BYU&ndash;Idaho in their local area</span></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="bodytxt" style="margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;">&nbsp;Tell the BYU&ndash;Idaho story</span></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="bodytxt" style="margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;"> Encourage prospective students to consider BYU-Idaho</span></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="bodytxt" style="margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;"> Share news of local alumni with the university and the Alumni Association (awards, marriages, promotions, anniversaries, deaths. etc.)</span></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="bodytxt" style="margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;"> Help identify local internship and employment opportunities for current students.</span></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="bodytxt" style="margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;"> Inform BYU&ndash;Idaho of questions and concerns alumni and others may have about the university.</span></span></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p class="bodytxt" style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;">For example, our Ambassadors recently identified two newly admitted students who had unique and special needs. Because of this advanced notice, on-campus entities such as Financial Aid were able to personally help these students even before they arrived on campus. Additionally, many students were encouraged to apply for the Regional Alumni Scholarship (an award for new freshman who are children of alumni). Last year over 50 students received this scholarship.</span></span></p>
<p class="bodytxt" style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;">The Alumni Association expresses a special thanks to our many volunteers who serve as local Alumni Ambassadors. Each day reaffirms how valuable they are as we strive to stay better connected with our alumni and bless the lives of our students. </span></span></p>
<p class="bodytxt" style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Franklin Gothic Book;"><span style="font-size: large;">If you would like more information about Alumni Ambassadors or other ways you can help support the Alumni Association, please call 1-800-537-2586 (1-800-LDS-alum) or send an e-mail to alumni@byui.edu.</span></span></p>
</td>
